The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Engineering firm Texmaco has reported a marginal rise of 3 per cent in turnover for the year ended March 31, 2010 at Rs 1,125.49 crore against Rs 1,091.25 crore a year ago. Gross profit (profit before depreciation and tax) jumped 23 per cent to Rs 150.51 crore from Rs 122.73 crore. The company registered a 23 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 93.04 crore against Rs 75.84 crore in the previous year.                             
	 Britannia Industries has reported a 9.3 per cent growth in sales at Rs 3,401.4 crore for the year ended March 31, 2010. Net profit declined 35.4 per cent to Rs 116.5 crore. The companys board of directors has recommended a dividend of 250 per cent and approved the sub-division of equity shares of face value Rs 10 to five shares of Rs 2 each.                             
	 Himadri Chemicals and Industries has reported a net profit of Rs 27.24 crore for the quarter ended March 31, 2010. The company had suffered a loss of Rs 20.29 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.                             
	 GPT Infraprojects has clocked a 53 per cent growth in its turnover at Rs 349 crore for the year ended March 31, 2010 against Rs 228 crore in the previous year. Earnings before interest, tax, depreciation and amortisation increased 130 per cent to Rs 56 crore from Rs 24 crore.                             
	 The Reserve Bank of India has awarded the first prize to Allahabad Bank for its house magazine  Triveni Dhara  in the bilingual house magazine competition held for the year 2008-09.                            
	 Coffee Day Xpress has launched six summer chillers in Calcutta. The chillers are priced between Rs 12 and Rs 25 and are available at all the Coffee Day Xpress outlets in the city.                             
	 Tata Teleservices has introduced the Special Tariff Voucher 199 Happy Sunday for its Tata Walky customers in Calcutta. The voucher offers special rates for calls to all networks and two hours of free talk time every Sunday.                             
	 HCL Infosystems has bagged an order to implement smart card-based solutions for the Public Distribution System in Chandigarh.                             
	 Bharti Airtel has entered into an exclusive partnership with Encyclopedia Britannica to offer a two-year free subscription of Britannica online, worth Rs 6,575, to all its broadband users.                             
	 Security product manufacturer Abus Padlock has launched its product  Padlocks  in the country, starting with Calcutta.
                                                                                                                                
